{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/tmp/tmp.6PsqNihqji","sessionId":"ede6160e-c98b-4fc1-8f61-fd0ff446d69c","version":"2.1.62","gitBranch":"master","agentId":"a260f5bd16defd39e","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"**Task:** Discover the orders API at http://localhost:8787 and retrieve all orders from 2026-02-09 to 2026-02-15 (inclusive).\n\n**Knowledge-base-first:** Semantic search is down. No KB docs exist for this service — proceed with discovery.\n\n**Approach:**\n1. Try common discovery endpoints: GET /, GET /api, GET /orders, GET /api/orders\n2. Look for date filtering params (e.g. ?start_date=2026-02-09&end_date=2026-02-15, or ?from=...&to=...)\n3. Once you find orders, return the full JSON response with all orders in that date range.\n\n**Scope:** Read-only HTTP queries to http://localhost:8787. No writes.\n\n**Bail-out rule:** If stuck after 10 tool calls, stop and return what you have.\n\n**Return contract:** Return:\n1. The working endpoint URL and params used\n2. The full JSON response of orders in the date range\n3. A summary of total quantities per product/SKU across all orders\n4. **Captures section:** (A) Snags — any API quirks, (B) Environment facts — base URL, endpoints, params, (C) Procedures — or 'none' for each\n"},"uuid":"da6b03c2-e3fa-4d9c-b0da-fa74a63d6e78","timestamp":"2026-02-27T11:04:35.775Z"}
{"parentUuid":"da6b03c2-e3fa-4d9c-b0da-fa74a63d6e78","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/tmp/tmp.6PsqNihqji","sessionId":"ede6160e-c98b-4fc1-8f61-fd0ff446d69c","version":"2.1.62","gitBranch":"master","agentId":"a260f5bd16defd39e","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<command-message>lore-semantic-search</command-message>\n<command-name>lore-semantic-search</command-name>\n<skill-format>true</skill-format>"},{"type":"text","text":"Base directory for this skill: /tmp/tmp.6PsqNihqji/.claude/skills/lore-semantic-search\n\n# Semantic Search Query (Local)\n\n**Preferred:** Use the `lore_search` MCP tool when available — it handles search + file reading in a single call. The methods below are fallbacks for environments without MCP support.\n\nWhen `docker.search` in `.lore/config.json` points to localhost or a private network, `Fetch`/`WebFetch` may fail due to URL restrictions.\n\n## Query Methods\n\n### Node.js (built-in fetch)\n\n```bash\nSEM_URL=\"http://localhost:PORT/search\" SEM_Q=\"your query\" SEM_K=5 \\\nnode -e \"const u=new URL(process.env.SEM_URL);u.searchParams.set('q',process.env.SEM_Q||'');u.searchParams.set('k',process.env.SEM_K||'8');fetch(u).then(r=>r.text()).then(t=>process.stdout.write(t)).catch(e=>{console.error(e.message);process.exit(1);});\"\n```\n\n### curl\n\n```bash\n# Default: returns file paths (paths_min mode)\ncurl -s \"http://localhost:PORT/search?q=your+query&k=5\"\n\n# Full mode: includes score and snippet per result\ncurl -s \"http://localhost:PORT/search?q=your+query&k=5&mode=full\"\n```\n\n## Checking Availability\n\n```bash\nnode -e \"const c=require('./.lore/harness/lib/config').getConfig('.');console.log(c.docker?.search ? JSON.stringify(c.docker.search) : 'unavailable')\"\n```\n\nIf output is `unavailable`, skip to Grep/Glob fallback immediately.\n\n## Snags\n\n- **MAX_K defaults to 2** — queries requesting `k` higher than `MAX_K` raise a validation error. Set `-e MAX_K=10` when starting the container.\n- **Paths in responses are relative** to the mounted volume root. Prepend the local mount path to read them.\n- **Model loading takes 30-60s on first start** — health returns `ok: true` only after indexing completes; poll before querying.\n- **WebFetch fails on localhost** — always use Bash (Node fetch or curl) for lore-docker endpoints.\n- Always include the `q` query parameter. Prefer short, concrete queries first, then broaden if needed.\n"}]},"uuid":"33bc3812-65d5-479b-8adb-e6a04764e6ff","timestamp":"2026-02-27T11:04:35.778Z"}
